parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended reverse acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates backwards without pressing the gas pedal
the vehicle accelerates in reverse despite applying the brakes
the vehicle takes off in reverse and only stops when hitting an obstacle
the vehicle picks up speed on an incline or uneven road surface.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate or soft brakes can increase stopping distances, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
brake pedal travels too far before engaging
brakes feel weak or unresponsive
increased stopping distance
vehicle takes longer to stop than expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Interference between Brake and Accelerator Pedals
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The close proximity of the brake and accelerator pedals can cause accidental simultaneous depression, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake and accelerator pedals are too close together
pedals are depressed simultaneously
unintended acceleration
loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger seatbelt retractor can prevent the seatbelt from functioning properly, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The front passenger seatbelt will not come out of the door
the seatbelt is stuck or jammed
the seatbelt cannot be extended or retracted.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Head Gasket Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to seize, leading to a complete loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine overheats
the engine loses power
the engine makes unusual noises
the engine oil and coolant mix
the vehicle stalls or fails to start
the head gasket blows
and the engine locks up.
